269/* OBJC_IS_CXX_KEYWORD recognizes the 'CXX_OBJC' keywords (such as
270 'class') which are shared in a subtle way between Objective-C and
271 C++. When the lexer is lexing in Objective-C/Objective-C++, if it
272 finds '@' followed by one of these identifiers (eg, '@class'), it
273 recognizes the whole as an Objective-C keyword. If the identifier
274 is found elsewhere, it follows the rules of the C/C++ language.
275 */
276#define OBJC_IS_CXX_KEYWORD(rid) \
277 (rid == RID_CLASS || rid == RID_SYNCHRONIZED \
278 || rid == RID_PUBLIC || rid == RID_PROTECTED || rid == RID_PRIVATE \
279 || rid == RID_TRY || rid == RID_THROW || rid == RID_CATCH)

385/* A token type for template-ids. If a template-id is processed while

1209inline omp_clause_mask
1210omp_clause_mask::operator << (int amount)
1211{
1212 omp_clause_mask ret;
1213 if (amount >= 64)
1214 {
1215 ret.low = 0;
1216 ret.high = low << (amount - 64);
1217 }
1218 else if (amount == 0)
1219 ret = *this;
1220 else
1221 {
1222 ret.low = low << amount;
1223 ret.high = (low >> (64 - amount)) | (high << amount);
1224 }
1225 return ret;
1226}

1228inline omp_clause_mask
1229omp_clause_mask::operator >> (int amount)
1230{
1231 omp_clause_mask ret;
1232 if (amount >= 64)
1233 {
1234 ret.low = high >> (amount - 64);
1235 ret.high = 0;
1236 }
1237 else if (amount == 0)
1238 ret = *this;
1239 else
1240 {
1241 ret.low = (high << (64 - amount)) | (low >> amount);
1242 ret.high = high >> amount;
1243 }
1244 return ret;
1245}

1307/* Return next tree in the chain for chain_next walking of tree nodes. */
1308static inline tree
1309c_tree_chain_next (tree t)
1310{
1311 /* TREE_CHAIN of a type is TYPE_STUB_DECL, which is different
1312 kind of object, never a long chain of nodes. Prefer
1313 TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT for types. */
1314 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (TREE_CODE (t), TS_TYPE_COMMON))
1315 return TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (t);
1316 /* Otherwise, if there is TREE_CHAIN, return it. */
1317 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (TREE_CODE (t), TS_COMMON))
1318 return TREE_CHAIN (t);
1319 return NULL;
1320}
